cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >
  If you use this software or its outputs in published research, please cite it
  using the metadata below.
type: software
title: "CONUS Hail Catastrophe Model"
version: 2.2.0
date-released: "2026-05-28"
abstract: >
  A radar-based probabilistic hail hazard model for the Continental United States.
  Ingests NOAA MYRORSS, NCAR GridRad, and NOAA MRMS radar-derived MESH data over
  a 28-year record (1998–present), applies bias correction and environmental
  filtering, fits regional Generalised Pareto Distribution tails via L-moments,
  and generates a 50,000-year stochastic event catalog on a 0.05° CONUS grid.
  Produces return-period hazard maps (10–50,000 years), occurrence probability
  rasters, and placeholder vulnerability curves for five construction classes.
authors:
